1
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:32,574
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION AND ALL NAMES,
CHARACTERS, PLACES, AND INCIDENTS

2
00:00:32,657 --> 00:00:35,410
ARE EITHER PRODUCTS OF THE AUTHOR'S
IMAGINATION OR ARE USED FICTITIOUSLY.

3
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:59,225
We're from the hit-and-run team
of Gongnam Police.

4
00:01:00,351 --> 00:01:01,728
The car involved belongs to this company,

5
00:01:01,811 --> 00:01:04,481
and I heard that a family member
of the chairman was in it.

6
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:06,483
I need to know who was driving that car.

7
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:08,401
Where can I meet the person in charge?

8
00:01:10,111 --> 00:01:12,906
An accident on Gongnam Road?
What are you talking about?

9
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,161
Mrs. Han.

10
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:24,584
Give me your phone.

11
00:01:36,596 --> 00:01:38,598
Are there any other traces of me anywhere?

12
00:01:38,681 --> 00:01:41,100
Do you have any texts or my number
on a computer or tablet?

13
00:01:43,019 --> 00:01:43,978
No, ma'am.

14
00:01:46,105 --> 00:01:49,317
Nobody can find out about what we did.

15
00:01:50,026 --> 00:01:50,860
If Yoon-gyeom,

16
00:01:51,611 --> 00:01:55,240
or especially my dad, finds out,
we're both dead.

17
00:01:56,282 --> 00:01:57,200
Do you understand?

18
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:00,620
What on earth has she done now?

19
00:02:00,703 --> 00:02:01,913
Why did it have to be now?

20
00:02:03,873 --> 00:02:06,084
I can't have
the task force team get exposed.

21
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:07,669
Change the location for the meeting.

22
00:02:07,752 --> 00:02:10,130
Make sure the press doesn't find out
that So-ra was in the car.

23
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:13,341
Don't let the police or any reporters
into the company building.

24
00:02:14,175 --> 00:02:15,009
Yes, sir.

25
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:28,648
Where's So-ra? Is she not home yet?

26
00:02:28,731 --> 00:02:31,317
She's going to stay at a hotel
until things die down, sir.

27
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:35,321
Why did she go out in the early morning
and hit somebody's car?

28
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:37,949
What the hell did she take?
Why is she acting so crazy?

29
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:39,993
Mr. Han.

30
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:41,161
Yoon-gyeom's here.

31
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:50,003
LY'S COMPANY VEHICLE FLEES THE SCENE
AFTER AN ACCIDENT ON GONGNAM ROAD

32
00:02:50,086 --> 00:02:51,462
Lee La-el.

33
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:56,092
I've underestimated you.

34
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:36,174
She might have to visit
the hit-and-run team at this rate.

35
00:03:36,257 --> 00:03:37,217
Where's So-ra?

36
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:39,928
Why are you looking for
your wife at my house?

37
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:41,679
Da-bi is waiting for her mother,

38
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:45,516
but the police came instead.

39
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:48,519
Do you not care about all this, Mr. Han?

40
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:50,521
You must've done a bad job
at managing your family.

41
00:03:51,105 --> 00:03:52,315
So this is my fault too?

42
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:56,694
Where's So-ra? Tell her to clean this up.

43
00:03:56,778 --> 00:03:58,238
-I don't know.
-Mr. Han!

44
00:03:59,197 --> 00:04:00,657
Come on.

45
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:03,660
You should work together
in a situation like this.

46
00:04:04,285 --> 00:04:05,703
She's at a hotel,

47
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:08,498
so I'll go get her.
You two can talk this out.

48
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:10,541
I'm sure that this isn't
that big of a deal.

49
00:04:12,168 --> 00:04:14,629
Early in the morning yesterday,
on a road in Gongnam-gu, Seoul,

50
00:04:14,712 --> 00:04:17,382
a strange car chase took place.

51
00:04:17,465 --> 00:04:20,385
Two cars were involved in a chase
on a relatively empty road

52
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:22,971
early in the morning,
as if it was a scene from a movie.

53
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:25,890
The two vehicles stopped
only after one crashed into the other.

54
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:27,976
You said it was Han Pan-ro?

55
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:29,310
What did he send?

56
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:49,747
Welcome.

57
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:52,208
It's good to see you.

58
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,794
I think Han Pan-ro knows

59
00:04:55,503 --> 00:04:57,755
that we tried to take
Yoon-gyeom's company shares.

60
00:04:57,839 --> 00:05:00,091
Oh, you didn't have to.

61
00:05:00,174 --> 00:05:01,926
Goodness. This is amazing.

62
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:03,052
A car should be comfortable.

63
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:08,933
Sir.

64
00:05:09,809 --> 00:05:12,854
I've got the footage of the hit-and-run.

65
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:15,773
The perpetrator was So-ra,

66
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:18,943
and she was with some man.

67
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:21,279
A man?

68
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:37,420
Find out who he is.

69
00:05:39,547 --> 00:05:42,550
And check Pan-ro's location too.

70
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:44,552
Quick.

71
00:05:45,136 --> 00:05:45,970
Yes, sir.

72
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,556
-Congratulations.
-Hello.

73
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:50,433
It must have been a long journey here.

74
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:52,351
You must've been busy writing your book.

75
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:53,811
Everything worked out, thanks to you.

76
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:57,106
-I think I've got to work harder.
-Thank you.

77
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:59,692
Hello, Congressman Seo!

78
00:06:01,402 --> 00:06:02,487
It's great to see you.

79
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:04,447
I've been wanting to meet with you.

80
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:07,533
It's nice to finally meet you,
Prime Minister Han.

81
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:11,079
We will mutually benefit
if we formally meet each other like this.

82
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:13,915
I'm happy about this too.

83
00:06:15,374 --> 00:06:16,667
Mr. Han.

84
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:21,672
Hello there, Mr. Kang.

85
00:06:24,425 --> 00:06:27,845
I would have given you a call
if I knew that you'd be here.

86
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:32,517
You're really going to act so friendly
after threatening me like that?

87
00:06:45,029 --> 00:06:47,115
I saw that So-ra was with another man.

88
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:52,370
What should I do about this video?

89
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:54,747
Does Yoon-gyeom know too?

90
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:57,792
Does he know that So-ra was with a man?

91
00:07:07,051 --> 00:07:09,011
Those people are so dramatic.

92
00:07:10,555 --> 00:07:11,889
The Financial Supervisory Commission

93
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:13,975
thinks that Mr. Kang
is planning something.

94
00:07:14,892 --> 00:07:17,103
Does La-el have
anything to do with this, sir?

95
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:20,773
I think so.

96
00:07:24,986 --> 00:07:26,821
LY GALLERY CLOSED

97
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:29,323
THE GALLERY IS CLOSED FOR TODAY
DUE TO PRIVATE ISSUES

98
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,640
A hit-and-run in the early morning?

99
00:07:56,225 --> 00:07:57,518
What the hell is this?

100
00:07:57,602 --> 00:07:59,770
I should get into accidents more often

101
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:03,357
if it'll make you come running right away.

102
00:08:05,651 --> 00:08:09,030
I accidentally hit a car
after I had some champagne with a friend.

103
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:12,742
It's nothing really. I was staying away
because it might become a mess.

104
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:14,118
Which friend?

105
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:19,665
Since when have we shared
so many personal details like that?

106
00:08:19,749 --> 00:08:20,958
You're seriously going to joke right now?

107
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:24,086
To be fair, although we don't know
each other's private lives,

108
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,380
we both know what we're like,
so why avoid the question?

109
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:29,884
But you need to answer my question first.

110
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:31,969
That's the order of things.

111
00:08:33,471 --> 00:08:35,640
I won't beat around the bush.

112
00:08:36,974 --> 00:08:38,434
Are you having an affair?

113
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,777
No.

114
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:58,412
What do you think our marriage is?

115
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:01,541
You know that this gallery

116
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,168
was a gift for
our fifth wedding anniversary, don't you?

117
00:09:04,252 --> 00:09:06,754
The presents for our
20th and 30th wedding anniversaries

118
00:09:07,463 --> 00:09:09,173
have all been decided on already.

119
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:12,218
I think I have the right

120
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:14,679
to get a present
on every wedding anniversary.

121
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:18,432
Our marriage

122
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:21,352
wasn't a coincidence
or an abstract concept.

123
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:24,855
I tried so hard to get you.

124
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:26,899
I made a plan, I made it work,

125
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:31,445
and I kept it going.

126
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:35,032
Our marriage…

127
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:41,872
is the result of my efforts.

128
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:44,417
So…

129
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,044
if somebody is trying to ruin it,

130
00:09:49,797 --> 00:09:51,465
then I can't forgive them.

131
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:54,260
Never.

132
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:02,310
Let me ask you one more time.

133
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:06,105
Are you having an affair?

134
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:12,111
No.

135
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:18,951
Your mouth says "no,"

136
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:21,037
but your eyes say "yes."

137
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:30,546
I've been hoping that it wouldn’t be true.

138
00:10:31,547 --> 00:10:34,008
No, not hoping. I've been praying.

139
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:39,388
So, the only question left is,

140
00:10:41,932 --> 00:10:43,893
-"who is it?"
-I told you, I'm not.

141
00:10:43,976 --> 00:10:46,020
I know exactly what I'm going to do now.

142
00:10:46,729 --> 00:10:48,022
I'm going to find out

143
00:10:49,565 --> 00:10:50,608
who your mistress is.

144
00:10:53,402 --> 00:10:55,404
-Mr. Kim.
-Yes, ma'am?

145
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:07,708
Well. I see that your conversation
didn't take very long.

146
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:08,834
That's a relief.

147
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:11,879
I'll take care of the cops.

148
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:15,257
Who do they think they are,
trying to investigate you?

149
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:18,302
Don't worry.

150
00:11:18,386 --> 00:11:20,179
I'll let them interrogate me.

151
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:21,389
Sorry?

152
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:23,516
Just make sure the reporters
don't take pictures when I go.

153
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:33,984
GONGNAM POLICE STATION

154
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:36,529
Ms. Oh, is it true that you used drugs?

155
00:11:36,612 --> 00:11:39,532
I moved the time for the singer
Oh Seon-hui's drug interrogation.

156
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:41,492
The chief says you don't need to worry.

157
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:42,785
He'll cover it up for you.

158
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:52,253
Go.

159
00:12:05,015 --> 00:12:07,935
CHIEF'S OFFICE

160
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:25,995
A lot of people
are curious about this case

161
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:28,497
since both the victim
and the perpetrator disappeared.

162
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:29,415
So…

163
00:12:29,498 --> 00:12:31,625
I had no choice but to investigate.

164
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:33,127
I hope you understand, Ms. Han.

165
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:35,045
It's fine.

166
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:37,631
I'm not here to be interrogated

167
00:12:38,132 --> 00:12:39,175
but to report somebody.

168
00:12:43,262 --> 00:12:44,472
Sorry?

169
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:45,598
The car that ran away…

170
00:12:47,349 --> 00:12:49,226
is mine. It was stolen.

171
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,315
Wait…

172
00:12:54,982 --> 00:12:55,983
So-ra?

173
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:58,944
That car belongs to you?

174
00:13:00,529 --> 00:13:02,114
Hold on, so…

175
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:04,825
You hit your own car?

176
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:08,704
My husband gave me the car that ran away.

177
00:13:09,205 --> 00:13:10,498
But it was stolen from me.

178
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:13,918
I was trying to catch the thief
before my husband found out,

179
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:15,336
but I guess I failed.

180
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:19,840
Everything will be fine

181
00:13:20,716 --> 00:13:22,343
once the police catches the driver.

182
00:13:24,428 --> 00:13:25,471
What?

183
00:13:25,554 --> 00:13:27,306
My car is wanted as a stolen vehicle?

184
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:35,523
Make sure that Sun-bin isn't exposed.

185
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:38,025
Hide the car,
and send the bodyguard abroad.

186
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:43,656
What?

187
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:47,868
Ms. Kim Sun-bin is
still not picking up her phone, sir.

188
00:14:01,715 --> 00:14:04,927
Open this when you feel lonely

189
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:06,554
and alone.

190
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:11,767
Inside this box, I've put my plan
to take care of everything.

191
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:18,125
MR. SEO

192
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:20,252
Mr. Seo.

193
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:22,254
You're doing okay, right?

194
00:15:23,547 --> 00:15:24,840
I think Pan-ro and Bon-geun

195
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:27,384
have been driven apart.

196
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:30,095
I thought you should know.

197
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:35,267
Do you want this to get even bigger?

198
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:39,605
Okay.

199
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:41,565
Whatever it is that you want,

200
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:43,776
I'll trust your decision.

201
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:56,246
You said that there would be a plan
inside the box that you gave me.

202
00:15:57,706 --> 00:15:59,249
There wasn't anything in there.

203
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,086
There is no plan, La-el.

204
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:05,881
Not having a plan is my plan.

205
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,051
I'll just stay by your side

206
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:11,804
like a shadow.

207
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:14,139
Just remember that I'm always with you

208
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:16,475
no matter what.

209
00:16:18,185 --> 00:16:19,144
What if I…

210
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,774
do something that only a monster would…

211
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:28,153
or…

212
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:32,866
something even worse?

213
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:35,828
Do it if you want.

214
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:37,788
It's okay.

215
00:16:49,091 --> 00:16:50,217
Hello, Chief Officer.

216
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:53,053
Did you catch the driver?

217
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:02,021
Could you tell me
the driver's phone number?

218
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:03,856
If they're an employee at LY,

219
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:06,233
then we'll punish them
and take care of everything.

220
00:17:52,362 --> 00:17:55,115
She was getting ready
to run away to another country.

221
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:57,910
Is she the right person?

222
00:17:58,869 --> 00:17:59,703
Yes.

223
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:06,126
Hey, miss.

224
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:08,087
I'll ask you this one last time.

225
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:12,758
Who did Chairman Kang tell you to protect?

226
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:36,365
Gosh, don't get any blood on me.

227
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:46,041
Move.

228
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:48,502
Oh, gosh…

229
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,174
Where's her phone?

230
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,260
Thanks.

231
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:22,452
A VIP?

232
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:20,010
LEE YEON-WOOK

233
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:36,735
LEE YEON-WOOK

234
00:20:49,289 --> 00:20:50,415
Who are you?

235
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:54,169
Who the hell are you?

236
00:20:55,545 --> 00:20:57,881
Who are you to be my husband's VIP?

237
00:21:05,013 --> 00:21:07,224
It'll be child's play
to find out who you are.

238
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:09,768
I can find you in one day.

239
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:18,527
Let's meet.

240
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:22,447
I'll go to you tomorrow at noon.

241
00:21:23,073 --> 00:21:23,949
However…

242
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:26,535
you must release the bodyguard right away.

243
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:53,145
Mr. Han,

244
00:21:53,895 --> 00:21:55,522
don't worry about the video.

245
00:21:56,231 --> 00:21:59,234
So-ra says that he's
a paid designated driver,

246
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:01,361
and revealing his identity
won't be a problem.

247
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:05,449
You said you can find out
who he is, right?

248
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:07,993
Yes, sir.

249
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:09,953
Yoon-gyeom, that bastard.

250
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:12,998
So he used me to threaten his own father?

251
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:15,709
You don't know what he's planning yet?

252
00:22:15,792 --> 00:22:17,711
No, but I'm in the process of finding out.

253
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:21,340
Once So-ra meets Yoon-gyeom
on Da-bi's birthday

254
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:22,883
and confirms a couple of things,

255
00:22:22,966 --> 00:22:24,259
I'll tell you what happened.

256
00:22:28,221 --> 00:22:29,264
I'll take it from here.

257
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:33,143
Today's a very important day, isn't it?

258
00:22:33,226 --> 00:22:36,188
You have Da-bi's birthday party
and the CMN parent interview.

259
00:22:36,271 --> 00:22:39,566
I'll make sure that you look like
the most graceful parent in the world.

260
00:22:39,649 --> 00:22:42,194
Since when did I like
looking like a parent?

261
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:45,155
Never, Ms. Han. I'm sorry.

262
00:22:46,323 --> 00:22:49,367
-Make me look tough.
-Yes, Ms. Han.

